    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-09-24T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-09-24T11:00:00-05:00" n="906"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d906">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/731: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-24T19:00:00+03:00"
                            >September 24, 1942—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 25—2:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>951. In course of a lengthy conversation yesterday with Prime Minister<note
                        n="98" xml:id="d906fn98">Sükrü Saraçoğlu, former Minister for Foreign
                        Affairs.</note> I brought matters enumerated below to his attention and
                    received following replies.</p>
                <p>1. Secret instruments which are part of equipment of United States Army bombers
                    interned in Turkey.</p>
                <p>Saraçoğlu gave peremptory instructions in my presence that interned aviators be
                    given access to instruments for purpose of delivering them to Embassy. Seals are
                    to be broken in presence of aviators and coding machines and codes are to be
                    delivered to Embassy. $15,000 of United States currency carried by planes is
                    likewise to be delivered to Embassy.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
